Introduction to API
An Application Programming Interface is a contract that allows code to talk to other code.APIs are the building blocks of modern software
because they allow for sharing of resources and services across applications, organizations,and devices.
Why are APIs important?
1. APIs help developers intergrate exciting features and build automation without reinventing the wheel
2.APIs allow enterprices to open up their product for faster innovation.
3.APIs can product themselves
Who works with APIs?
API use is not limited to the tech and IT industries.Survey responses in the report show that while tech,business,IT,
and banking sectors represent the bulk of API use, any industry can benefit from the convenience provided by APIs
